description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are recruiting a registered nurse who has an interest in wound care for a great opportunity to develop further knowledge and skills as a Tissue Viability Community Nurse.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be a registered nurse with core community nursing skills, who would like to further develop their skills and after training act as an expert resource within the tissue viability specialty.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be working under the supervision of Clinical Advisor for pressure relief/tissue viability nurses along with the support of the community nursing locality team manager. Your main role will be working within a specified locality in Portsmouth supporting registered and unregistered staff to achieve competency, skill and experience with Tissue Viability whilst improving the care and management of patients in line with national guidance. Rotation into a planned Leg Ulcer Clinic Hub would also be part the future role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will be expected to maintain clinical skills and competence, you will have the ability to work unsupervised, be able to prioritise your workload, have excellent communication skills and the interest and enthusiasm to promote best practice in tissue viability. As a team player, you’ll be able to prioritise your work in order to meet deadlines and have a customer focused approach&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Experience in the field of adult wound care within the community or hospital is desirable but a willingness to learn and contribute is more important. The role will be Monday to Friday (except bank holidays) between 08.30 to 17.00 hours, full time hours. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contact us today&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more information about these roles or to come and visit our service please contact Debbie Patten – Clinical Matron on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;debbie.patten@solent.nhs.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; or 07770 641951&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note that should this post attract sufficient interest, we may choose to close at an earlier date. We strongly suggest that you apply at an early stage.&lt;strong&gt;If we have not contacted you within four weeks of the closing date of this post, please presume that you have not been selected.&lt;/strong&gt;Candidates selected for interview will be contacted within 2-3 weeks; therefore you should check your emails regularly including junk mail folders&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
